Dosa's Chennai Chicken

8 pieces boneless chicken breast or thigh (~4lbs)
4 c plain yogurt
3" ginger, chopped
6 cloves garlic, chopped
1 c red onions, chopped
1/2 c green onions, chopped for garnish
1/4 c mint leaves, chopped
3/4 c cilantro, chopped (1/2 c for marinade + 1/4 c for garnish)
2 tsp chili powder
1 dried red chile
2 tsp cumin, ground
2 tsp coriander, ground
1 tsp black pepper, ground
1 tsp tumeric
2 tbsp lemon juice
1/2 each lime wedge
3 tbsp cornstarch
2 eggs 
salt to taste
oil for frying

Cut the chicken into bite sized strips. Blend the yogurt, ginger, garlic, red onions, cilantro, mint leaves, curry leaves, and the spices (chili, cumin, pepper, dried chiles, coriander, tumeric). Add salt to taste. Marinate the chicken in the fridge overnight (or min 2-4hrs). Before frying, add cornstarch and eggs and mix well. Add the lemon juice and mix. Heat oil on high until hot. Fry chicken until it;s slightly golden brown. Drain the oil and let chicken rest on paper towel. Serve garnished with cilantro and green onions.
